"I will cross the seven oceans for you."

232
00:10:10,349 --> 00:10:12,025
If I say this to someone,

233
00:10:12,025 --> 00:10:14,869
it doesn't mean that I will literally 
cross the seven oceans for them.

234
00:10:14,869 --> 00:10:17,685
Or that Saurabh is literally 
carrying a mountain on his shoulders.

235
00:10:17,685 --> 00:10:20,375
The metaphor means that he is very hardworking.

236
00:10:20,375 --> 00:10:23,523
Crossing the seven oceans means 
that I will put all my heart and soul into it.

237
00:10:23,523 --> 00:10:25,481
Apart from this, it is also possible that

238
00:10:25,481 --> 00:10:29,043
while writing Ramayan, the Atishayokti Alankar was used.

239
00:10:29,043 --> 00:10:36,274
In literature, writers and poets often 
exaggerate while describing real events.

240
00:10:36,274 --> 00:10:38,902
For example, have you seen the Hollywood film 300?

241
00:10:38,902 --> 00:10:40,961
In this film, a historic battle has been shown

242
00:10:40,961 --> 00:10:42,655
between the Persians and the Greeks.

243
00:10:43,282 --> 00:10:46,418
